$interpreted: : Three days later
Jahan: (Owww, neck still hurts like hell. That bastard...)
Jahan: By the way, old geezer Vincent sure is taking his sweet time. Bet he's just trying to milk as much as he can out of this...)
Jahan: Good work, Sir Vincent.
Jahan: That financial officer only looks at the numbers. He knows nothing about the difficulties you face.
Douglas: None of your business, now get out of my way!
Jahan: Hmph, cranky old snob.
Jahan: Your Majesty Regent Theodore, Jahan here to report something important.
Theodore: Speak.
Jahan: Jahan was interrogating the assassin with Sir Dylan. However, during the interrogation, the assassin blurted out something quite offensive...
Jahan: Such shameless words must be reported to Your Majesty!
Jahan: The wings of the Half-Blood...shall swipe away the imposter blocking the Sun.
Theodore: ......
Jahan: Your Majesty, as soon as your loyal servant heard this, I immediately came to report in fear that it might damage your reputation.
Jahan: Do you want me to handle this for you?
Theodore: Who else knows about this?
Jahan: Nothing to worry about, Your Majesty. Besides Sir Dylan, only I know about it.
Jahan: M-My sincere gratitude your Majesty. Is it that you realize my lack of training and...*cough*...have decided to train me yourself? But...
Jahan: Your loyal servant...might be unable to handle it...if it dirties your precious hands...
Theodore: What are you saying?
Jahan: ...*cough*...dirty deeds, should be done by those who are willing to get their hands dirty. That way, your Majesty's hands can be kept squeaky clean...
Jahan: *cough*...*cough*...thank you, your Majesty...
Theodore: That nonsense the assassin spewed, I don't want a third person besides the two of us to know about it.
Jahan: Your Majesty, do you mean that you want Sir Dylan...
Theodore: Think about it. If you value your life, you had better prove your worth to me.
